[00:49.39]"'Enter,' said De Lacey, 'and I will try in what manner I can to relieve your wants;  but, unfortunately, my children are from home, and as I am blind, I am afraid I shall find it difficult to procure food for you.' 
“’进来吧，‘德拉赛说，’我很愿意竭力满足您的需要，但是不巧的是，我的孩子们都出门去了，而我眼睛又看不见，所以我恐怕很难为您准备什么食物。‘”

[01:00.72]"'Do not trouble yourself, my kind host; I have food; it is warmth and rest only that I need.' 
“’不用麻烦，好心的主人。我自己有吃的东西，我只需要烤烤火，再稍微休息一下。‘”

[01:06.88]"I sat down, and a silence ensued.   I knew that every minute was precious to me, yet I remained irresolute in what manner to commence the interview, when the old man addressed me. 
